BT /F2 21 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 744 Tm (AspieDad Communication Guide) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 726 Tm (A one-page summary with practical communication help for both NT and Aspie readers.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 694 Tm (Helpful framing about speaking and processing) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 676 Tm (It is not always true that NT people talk more than Aspie people.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 662 Tm (But in emotional conversations, NT spouses may verbalize more while Aspie spouses) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 648 Tm (often process more internally or need shorter, clearer pieces of information.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 618 Tm (A helpful way to say this to an NT reader) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 600 Tm (Long emotional monologues may be lost quickly, not because I do not care,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 586 Tm (but because I process best in shorter, clearer parts with time to respond.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 552 Tm (3 Helpful Tactics For NT Readers) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 534 Tm (1. Be direct and specific.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 102 520 Tm (Say the real need clearly instead of hinting or expecting it to be inferred.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 502 Tm (2. Acknowledge before solving.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 102 488 Tm (If the moment is emotional, let the Aspie person know what matters first, then move to fixes.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 470 Tm (3. Use one issue at a time.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 102 456 Tm (Keeping the conversation narrow reduces overload and improves the chance of being understood.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 424 Tm (3 Helpful Tactics For Aspie Readers) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 406 Tm (1. Say the care out loud.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 102 392 Tm (Do not assume your love or concern is obvious. NT spouses often need it spoken clearly.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 374 Tm (2. Acknowledge feelings before facts.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 102 360 Tm (Start with: "I can see this hurt you" before moving into logic, analysis, or correction.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 342 Tm (3. Return after processing.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 102 328 Tm (If you need time, say so directly and come back. Silence without return can feel like rejection.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 296 Tm (3 Simple Phrases For NT Readers) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 280 Tm (1. "Can you tell me what you heard me say?") Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 266 Tm (2. "I am not hinting. What I need is...") Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 252 Tm (3. "We can stay with one issue at a time.") Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 224 Tm (3 Simple Phrases For Aspie Readers) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 208 Tm (1. "I care about you, even if I am struggling to show it.") Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 194 Tm (2. "I need a few minutes to process, but I will come back.") Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 84 180 Tm (3. "Do you want comfort, help, or for me just to listen?") Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 88 Tm (AspieDad.com | Building understanding between NT and Aspie family life) Tj ET
